Motjeka Madisha during the 2021 Africa Cup of Nations Qualifiers South Africa training session. JOHANNESBURG - Messages of condolences continue to flow onto social media following the passing of Mamelodi Sundowns defender, Motjeka Madisha at the weekend. PSL clubs and local personalties have expressed their sympathies on Twitter. The Brazilians are yet to release a statement. It is almost 24-hours since the Bafana Bafana defender was involved in a fatal car crash. WATCH: Anele Ngcongca laid to rest Former Sundowns coach Pitso Mosimane is among those who've sent their condolences on Twitter. Current co-coach at the club, Rulani Mokoena  recalled the last moments he shared with the 25-year-old talent. Madisha's passing follows that of another defender, Anele Ngcongca. He also passed away in a deadly accident and was buried this past week.